## What This Script Does

`asm_enterprise.py` automates 12 of the 14 phases defined in the Enterprise Financial Services ASM SOP. At runtime you choose which phases to run and the script:

- Prompts you for: root domains, IP/CIDR ranges, org name, ASN, GitHub org handle, and API keys
- Presents a numbered phase menu -- run all at once or cherry-pick
- Executes each selected phase in sequence, invoking the appropriate tools
- Writes all output to a timestamped directory: `output/<domain>_<YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS>/`
- Generates a consolidated `SUMMARY_REPORT.json` at the end

**Active phases** (3, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11) send network requests to targets. The script will ask for explicit authorization confirmation before any active scanning.

---

## What Is NOT Automated

| Phase / Feature | Reason | Manual Action |
|---|---|---|
| **Phase 12 -- Third-Party & Supply Chain** | Vendor/SaaS lists cannot be enumerated externally | Request procurement records and OAuth consent logs from target IT |
| **Phase 13 -- M&A Pre-Acquisition** | Composite of other phases in passive-only mode | Run Phases 2, 3, 6, 7, 9, 10, 11 and decline all active scanning prompts |
| **Dark Web / Flashpoint** | Requires enterprise license + API key | Configure keyword Collections in Flashpoint portal within 24hr of deal close |
| **Cloud Posture w/ Credentials (ScoutSuite/Prowler)** | Requires provisioned cloud credentials | `prowler aws -g cis_level2` or `python3 scout.py aws` once keys are available |
| **SOAR / PagerDuty / ServiceNow integration** | Platform-specific tokens + webhook config | Use `notify` tool: `cat findings.txt \| notify -provider slack` |
| **HaveIBeenPwned Enterprise domain API** | Paid API key required | Public breach list IS checked; add `hibp_api_key` to config for domain-level data |
| **DeHashed / IntelX / SecurityTrails** | Paid subscriptions | Subscribe and add API keys; integrate manually into downstream queries |
| **IMDSv2 enforcement** | Requires AWS credentials + console access | `aws ec2 modify-instance-metadata-options --instance-id i-xxx --http-tokens required` |

---

## Requirements Overview

### Python Libraries (pip3)

| Library | Purpose | Required? |
|---|---|---|
| `requests` | HTTP queries: crt.sh, ARIN, ipinfo.io, HIBP, CISA KEV | YES |
| `dnspython` | DNS resolution, AXFR, CNAME analysis | YES |
| `rich` | Terminal UI | YES |
| `shodan` | Shodan API integration | YES (for Phases 2, 4, 5, 9) |
| `censys` | Censys API integration | YES (for Phases 2, 5) |
| `certstream` | Real-time CT log monitoring | YES (for Phase 14 only) |

### System / External Tools (installed separately)

| Tool | Used In | Install Command |
|---|---|---|
| `subfinder` | Phase 3 | `go install -v github.com/projectdiscovery/subfinder/v2/cmd/subfinder@latest` |
| `amass` | Phase 3 | `apt install amass` or `snap install amass` |
| `puredns` | Phase 3 | `go install github.com/d3mondev/puredns/v2@latest` |
| `dnsx` | Phase 3 | `go install github.com/projectdiscovery/dnsx/cmd/dnsx@latest` |
| `massdns` | Phase 3, 4 | `apt install massdns` |
| `dnsrecon` | Phase 3 | `apt install dnsrecon` |
| `masscan` | Phase 5 | `apt install masscan` |
| `nmap` | Phase 5 | `apt install nmap` (pre-installed on Kali) |
| `httpx` | Phase 6 | `go install github.com/projectdiscovery/httpx/cmd/httpx@latest` |
| `tlsx` | Phase 6 | `go install github.com/projectdiscovery/tlsx/cmd/tlsx@latest` |
| `nuclei` | Phases 7, 8, 10, 11 | `go install github.com/projectdiscovery/nuclei/v3/cmd/nuclei@latest` |
| `subjack` | Phase 7 | `go install github.com/haccer/subjack@latest` |
| `whatweb` | Phase 8 | `apt install whatweb` |
| `gau` | Phase 8 | `go install github.com/lc/gau/v2/cmd/gau@latest` |
| `cloud_enum` | Phase 9 | See below |
| `trufflehog` | Phase 11 | See below |
| `gitleaks` | Phase 11 | `apt install gitleaks` |

**The script gracefully skips any tool that is not installed.** It will warn you and continue. You do not need every tool installed for the script to run -- just the ones relevant to your selected phases.

