## Full Installation (Kali Linux)

### Step 1 -- Update and install system tools

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Core tools (most pre-installed on Kali)
sudo apt install -y \
    python3 python3-pip \
    nmap masscan massdns \
    amass dnsrecon whatweb \
    whois curl jq git \
    gitleaks

# Verify Python version (need 3.9+)
python3 --version
```

### Step 2 -- Install Go (required for ProjectDiscovery tools)

```bash
# Check if Go is already installed
go version

# If not installed:
wget https://go.dev/dl/go1.22.4.linux-amd64.tar.gz
sudo tar -C /usr/local -xzf go1.22.4.linux-amd64.tar.gz
echo 'export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin:$HOME/go/bin' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
go version
```

### Step 3 -- Install ProjectDiscovery tools

```bash
# subfinder
go install -v github.com/projectdiscovery/subfinder/v2/cmd/subfinder@latest

# httpx
go install -v github.com/projectdiscovery/httpx/cmd/httpx@latest

# dnsx
go install -v github.com/projectdiscovery/dnsx/cmd/dnsx@latest

# nuclei
go install -v github.com/projectdiscovery/nuclei/v3/cmd/nuclei@latest

# tlsx
go install -v github.com/projectdiscovery/tlsx/cmd/tlsx@latest

# puredns
go install github.com/d3mondev/puredns/v2@latest

# subjack
go install github.com/haccer/subjack@latest

# gau
go install github.com/lc/gau/v2/cmd/gau@latest

# Update Nuclei templates immediately after install
nuclei -update-templates

# Verify all are in PATH
for tool in subfinder httpx dnsx nuclei tlsx puredns subjack gau; do
    which $tool && echo "$tool: OK" || echo "$tool: MISSING"
done
```

### Step 4 -- Install cloud_enum

```bash
cd /opt
git clone https://github.com/initstring/cloud_enum
cd cloud_enum
pip3 install -r requirements.txt
sudo ln -s /opt/cloud_enum/cloud_enum.py /usr/local/bin/cloud_enum
chmod +x /opt/cloud_enum/cloud_enum.py
```

### Step 5 -- Install trufflehog

```bash
curl -sSfL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/trufflesecurity/trufflehog/main/scripts/install.sh \
  | sudo sh -s -- -b /usr/local/bin
trufflehog --version
```

### Step 6 -- Install Python dependencies for this script

```bash
cd /path/to/asm_enterprise
pip3 install -r requirements.txt

# Verify key libraries loaded
python3 -c "import requests, dns, rich, shodan, censys, certstream; print('All core libs OK')"
```

### Step 7 -- Clone this script

```bash
git clone <your-repo>  # or just copy asm_enterprise.py to your working directory
cd asm_enterprise
chmod +x asm_enterprise.py
```

### Optional -- Install ScoutSuite and Prowler (for Phase 9 authenticated cloud assessment)

```bash
# ScoutSuite
pip3 install scoutsuite

# Prowler
pip3 install prowler
# or
git clone https://github.com/prowler-cloud/prowler
cd prowler && pip3 install .
```

